President Obama has proclaimed October 17-23, 2010 as National Forest Products Week, in recognition of the importance of forests and their products in the growth and development of the United States. He highlights the value of forests as sustainable resources that provide clean water and air, wood, wildlife habitats, recreational opportunities, and beautiful surroundings. The proclamation emphasizes the need to conserve forests for future generations and mentions the America's Great Outdoors Initiative, which aims to protect the country's natural heritage. The president also acknowledges the economic contributions of forest management and restoration, as well as the potential for innovation and growth in industries related to forest products. The proclamation concludes by calling on Americans to celebrate the various uses and products of forests and to appreciate those who steward these resources.